sentences: Loney Dear is the pseudonym of Swedish singer-songwriter and multi-instrumentalist Emil Svanängen (born March 29, 1979).
His first major release came in February, 2007 in the U.S. when Sub Pop re-issued his album Loney, Noir.
Emil Svanängen self-released his first album, The Year of River Fontana, in 2003.
Loney, Dear appeared on the song "This Boy" from I'm From Barcelona's 2006 album Let Me Introduce My Friends.
In 2006, Loney, Dear was signed by U.S. record label Sub Pop.
Sub Pop released Loney, Dear's fourth album, Loney, Noir, on February 6, 2007.
In 2009, Loney, Dear joined Andrew Bird as he toured to support Bird's January release of Noble Beast.
In 2017, Svanängen was signed to Peter Gabriel's Real World Records.
In 2021, Loney Dear released the album 'A Lantern and a Bell' on Real World Records.
